Data Visualization Project Plan

Jing Ye, Yiqing Jin, Denis Tan

28 February 2015

Topic: Energy Demand Forecasting

Research Question

We hope to visualize current energy demand and forecast future energy demand for various cities worldwide by using time series data on existing hour demand and other publicly available factor variables. We are considering various models, such as time series methods, machine learning methods, econometric methods, to apply and have not settled on a set methodology yet.

Data Source

Our data is obtained from https://github.com/ecohen4/energy which has a database of energy demand for almost 40 cities across the world. We have forked the repository. A snapshot of the available data is provided in Figure 1.
